data.chText: 劫持（交通工具，尤指飞机）
data.enText: to use violence or threats to take control of a vehicle, especially a plane, in order to force it to travel to a different place or to demand sth from a government

data.chText: 飞机在从伦敦飞往罗马途中遭到两名持械男子劫持。
data.enText: The plane was hijacked by two armed men on a flight from London to Rome.

data.chText: 操纵（会议等，以推销自己的意图）
data.enText: to use or take control of sth, especially a meeting, in order to advertise your own aims and interests

data.chText: 这个地区最近发生了一连串劫持事件。
data.enText: There have been a series of hijackings recently in the area.

means: 劫持(交通工具，尤指飞机)
操纵(会议等，以推销自己的意图)

tr: seizure of a vehicle in transit either to rob it or divert it to an alternate destination

example: The Cubans commandeered the plane and flew it to Miami

value.def: If someone hijacks a plane or other vehicle, they illegally take control of it by force while it is travelling from one place to another.

example.ex: Two men tried to hijack a plane on a flight from Riga to Murmansk...
example.tran: 两名男子试图劫持一架从里加飞往摩尔曼斯克的飞机。

example.ex: A Korean airliner was hijacked by two passengers and forced to fly to Tashkent...
example.tran: 一架韩国的大型客机被两名乘客劫持，被迫飞往塔什干。

example.ex: The hijacked plane exploded in a ball of fire.
example.tran: 被劫持的飞机爆炸,变成了一团火球。

example.ex: Every minute during the hijack seemed like a week.
example.tran: 被劫持过程中，每一分钟都过得如同一周那么漫长。

value.tran: 劫持（飞机或其他交通工具）

example.ex: Car hijackings are running at a rate of nearly 50 a day.
example.tran: 劫车事件的发生率高达每天近50起。

value.def: If you say that someone has hijacked something, you disapprove of the way in which they have taken control of it when they had no right to do so.

example.ex: A peaceful demonstration had been hijacked by anarchists intent on causing trouble.
example.tran: 和平示威已遭到蓄意制造事端的无政府主义者的操控。
